The site object contains a representation of the complete website
(with references to the actual files that are used)

Generation goes like this:
- build site tree from dir tree
- transform tree to output dir tree

page represents a page object
page:
	- name
	- id
	- sort_order
	- <current macro list>
	- <current options list>
	- output directory name

	these must be added with page.add<name>(object)
	- <child page list>
	- <contents list>
	- <file list>

content represents 1 .page file
content:
	- input .page file
	- name
	- sort order
	- id
	- output file name

file:
	- input file name
	?- type

		